sql:
SELECT AVG(hdi_value) AS average_hdi
FROM hdi_data
WHERE country_id = 1 AND year = 2020;

SELECT country_name, hdi_rank
FROM countries
ORDER BY hdi_rank DESC;

external_knowledge:
- 'Dawn of the 90s' refers to the year 1990;
- 'Twilight of the 15th year of the 21st century' refers to the year 2015;
- 'Sailing path' metaphorically represents the progression and changes in HDI values over time;
- 'Waypoints' metaphorically signify the specific dimensions and indicators that contribute to the HDI value.

- 'HDI performers' refers to countries with the highest Human Development Index (HDI) values. ;
- The query aims to highlight the top average HDI values for different dimensions and indicators, which could help in assessing the developmental trends of various countries. ;
- 'Top 3' here means the three highest average HDI values for each country, dimension, and indicator combination. ;
- The HDI is a composite statistic of life expectancy, education, and per capita income indicators, which are used to rank countries into four tiers of human development. ;
- The years covered by the data show the progress or decline in HDI values for each country, dimension, and indicator combination. ;

